               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380618-name-146" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-146" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-146" type="surname" value="WAKEFIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-146" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>FRANCIS WAKEFIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Old Broad-street, and am a stock<lb></lb>broker. On Tuesday, the 14th of May, in the afternoon, I was passing Finsbury-place—I received information from a boy—I turned, and missed my handkerchief—this is it—(<hi rend="italic">looking at one</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380618-name-147" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-147" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-147" type="surname" value="BAGNELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380618-name-147" type="given" value="CHARLES HENRY"></interp>CHARLES HENRY BAGNELL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant F</hi> 31.) I was passing along, and saw the prisoner running from Finsbury-square into Wilson-street—I pursued, and saw him drop this handkerchief from his right hand—I took it and took him—I went to the prosecutor, who claimed it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> How many were running besides me? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I suppose a dozen, but you were the first, and you dropped this handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I did not throw it down—I was running with the mob—I was lost sight of two or three times.</p>
